  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Human rights film festival &#x201C;Inconvenient Films 2017&#x201C;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to use human rights documentary film festival &#x201E;Inconvenient Films&#x201C; as a tool for large&#x2014;scale awareness raising campaign, informing Lithuanian society about global challenges and importance of development cooperation. Educational events of the project will encourage participants to reflect on global issues, and engage into dialogue about the needs of the developing countries. The project will place particular emphasis on the situation in the Middle East region as well as EU Eastern Partnership states.
In the framework of the project an educational program of at least 30 award-winning documentary films will be created in cooperation with international partners and promoted nation-wide, film screenings will be accompanied by roundtable discussions with policy-makers and activists, Q&#x2019;n&#x2019;A sections with filmmakers and experts. Significant part of the projects activities will be aimed at young people.</narrative>
  </description>
